  "slug": "diagnostic-categories-as-systems",
  "type": "html",
  "title": "Compounding Error in Chains",
  "concept": "A classification mistake at the start of a sequential process doesn't stay small—each step trusts the previous one, so a 20% error at the entry becomes a 59% error four steps later, making the first decision the highest-leverage point in any chain of dependent actions.",
  "interactiveId": "78ecc98d-b3e9-4b28-ae74-4a3c7cb1508a",
  "sourcePieceId": "35cc7ceb-6d53-4db5-a76e-7dac2ea9e03b",
  "publishedAt": 1778681295190,
  "voiceScore": 95,
  "content": {
    "type": "html",
    "html": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n<title>Compounding Error in Chains</title>\n<style>\n  :root {\n    --bg: #faf7f1;\n    --fg: #1a1a1a;\n    --muted: #6b6b6b;\n    --line: #e5e0d6;\n    --correct: #1a6b62;\n    --error: #c9a227;\n  }\n  * { box-sizing: border-box; }\n  body {\n    font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, \"Segoe UI\", sans-serif;\n    margin: 0;\n    padding: 20px;\n    color: var(--fg);\n    background: var(--bg);\n    line-height: 1.5;\n  }\n  h2 {\n    font-size: 1.05rem;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    margin: 0 0 4px;\n  }\n  p.subhead {\n    margin: 0 0 20px;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n  }\n  .control {\n    display: flex;\n    align-items: center;\n    gap: 14px;\n    margin-bottom: 24px;\n  }\n  .control label {\n    font-weight: 500;\n    flex-shrink: 0;\n  }\n  .control input[type=range] {\n    flex: 1;\n    accent-color: var(--correct);\n    min-width: 120px;\n  }\n  .control output {\n    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    min-width: 3ch;\n    text-align: right;\n  }\n  .chain {\n    margin: 24px 0;\n    padding: 20px;\n    background: #fff;\n    border: 1px solid var(--line);\n    border-radius: 8px;\n  }\n  .link {\n    margin-bottom: 16px;\n    padding-bottom: 16px;\n    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);\n  }\n  .link:last-child {\n    margin-bottom: 0;\n    padding-bottom: 0;\n    border-bottom: none;\n  }\n  .link-label {\n    font-size: 0.75rem;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    text-transform: uppercase;\n    letter-spacing: 0.06em;\n    margin-bottom: 8px;\n    display: flex;\n    justify-content: space-between;\n    align-items: center;\n  }\n  .link-label .error-rate {\n    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    color: var(--error);\n  }\n  .link-bar {\n    display: flex;\n    height: 32px;\n    border-radius: 4px;\n    overflow: hidden;\n    background: var(--line);\n  }\n  .segment {\n    display: flex;\n    align-items: center;\n    justify-content: center;\n    font-size: 0.8rem;\n    font-weight: 500;\n    color: #fff;\n    transition: flex 200ms ease-out;\n  }\n  .segment.correct {\n    background: var(--correct);\n  }\n  .segment.error {\n    background: var(--error);\n  }\n  .reading {\n    margin: 18px 0 6px;\n    padding: 10px 14px;\n    background: var(--bg);\n    border: 1px solid var(--line);\n    border-radius: 6px;\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n  }\n  .reading strong {\n    font-weight: 600;\n  }\n  p.caption {\n    margin: 14px 0 0;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    font-size: 0.875rem;\n  }\n  @media (max-width: 480px) {\n    .control {\n      flex-direction: column;\n      align-items: flex-start;\n    }\n    .control input[type=range] {\n      width: 100%;\n    }\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h2>Drag to set the error rate at the start</h2>\n<p class=\"subhead\">Watch how a small mistake compounds through four sequential steps that trust each other.</p>\n\n<div class=\"control\">\n  <label for=\"error-rate\">Starting error:</label>\n  <input id=\"error-rate\" type=\"range\" min=\"0\" max=\"50\" value=\"20\" aria-describedby=\"error-out\">\n  <output id=\"error-out\" for=\"error-rate\">20</output><span>%</span>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"chain\">\n  <div class=\"link\">\n    <div class=\"link-label\">\n      <span>Step 1</span>\n      <span class=\"error-rate\" id=\"err1\">20%</span>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"link-bar\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n      <div class=\"segment correct\" data-link=\"1\"></div>\n      <div class=\"segment error\" data-link=\"1\"></div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"link\">\n    <div class=\"link-label\">\n      <span>Step 2</span>\n      <span class=\"error-rate\" id=\"err2\">36%</span>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"link-bar\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n      <div class=\"segment correct\" data-link=\"2\"></div>\n      <div class=\"segment error\" data-link=\"2\"></div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"link\">\n    <div class=\"link-label\">\n      <span>Step 3</span>\n      <span class=\"error-rate\" id=\"err3\">49%</span>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"link-bar\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n      <div class=\"segment correct\" data-link=\"3\"></div>\n      <div class=\"segment error\" data-link=\"3\"></div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"link\">\n    <div class=\"link-label\">\n      <span>Step 4</span>\n      <span class=\"error-rate\" id=\"err4\">59%</span>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"link-bar\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n      <div class=\"segment correct\" data-link=\"4\"></div>\n      <div class=\"segment error\" data-link=\"4\"></div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"reading\">\n  Final error: <strong id=\"final-error\">59</strong>%.\n  Amplification: <strong id=\"amplification\">×2.95</strong>.\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"caption\" id=\"caption\">A 20% error at the start becomes 59% by the fourth step. Each link trusts the previous one, so mistakes compound instead of staying small.</p>\n\n<script>\n  (function () {\n    var slider = document.getElementById('error-rate');\n    var errorOut = document.getElementById('error-out');\n    var finalErrorOut = document.getElementById('final-error');\n    var amplificationOut = document.getElementById('amplification');\n    var caption = document.getElementById('caption');\n    \n    var links = [\n      {\n        correct: document.querySelector('[data-link=\"1\"].correct'),\n        error: document.querySelector('[data-link=\"1\"].error'),\n        label: document.getElementById('err1')\n      },\n      {\n        correct: document.querySelector('[data-link=\"2\"].correct'),\n        error: document.querySelector('[data-link=\"2\"].error'),\n        label: document.getElementById('err2')\n      },\n      {\n        correct: document.querySelector('[data-link=\"3\"].correct'),\n        error: document.querySelector('[data-link=\"3\"].error'),\n        label: document.getElementById('err3')\n      },\n      {\n        correct: document.querySelector('[data-link=\"4\"].correct'),\n        error: document.querySelector('[data-link=\"4\"].error'),\n        label: document.getElementById('err4')\n      }\n    ];\n\n    function update() {\n      var initialError = +slider.value / 100;\n      errorOut.textContent = Math.round(initialError * 100);\n      \n      var cumulativeErrors = [];\n      for (var i = 0; i < 4; i++) {\n        var cumulativeError = 1 - Math.pow(1 - initialError, i + 1);\n        cumulativeErrors.push(cumulativeError);\n      }\n      \n      links.forEach(function (link, idx) {\n        var errFrac = cumulativeErrors[idx];\n        var correctFrac = 1 - errFrac;\n        link.correct.style.flex = correctFrac.toFixed(4);\n        link.error.style.flex = errFrac.toFixed(4);\n        \n        var correctPct = Math.round(correctFrac * 100);\n        var errPct = Math.round(errFrac * 100);\n        link.correct.textContent = correctPct >= 15 ? correctPct + '%' : '';\n        link.error.textContent = errPct >= 15 ? errPct + '%' : '';\n        link.label.textContent = errPct + '%';\n      });\n      \n      var finalError = Math.round(cumulativeErrors[3] * 100);\n      finalErrorOut.textContent = finalError;\n      \n      var amp = initialError > 0 ? (cumulativeErrors[3] / initialError) : 1;\n      amplificationOut.textContent = '×' + amp.toFixed(2);\n      \n      if (initialError === 0) {\n        caption.textContent = 'Zero error at the start means zero error at the end. The chain stays clean.';\n      } else if (initialError <= 0.10) {\n        caption.textContent = 'A small error at the start grows through the chain. Each step inherits what came before, so the final result drifts further from correct.';\n      } else if (initialError <= 0.25) {\n        caption.textContent = 'A 20% error at the start becomes 59% by the fourth step. Each link trusts the previous one, so mistakes compound instead of staying small.';\n      } else if (initialError <= 0.40) {\n        caption.textContent = 'When the first step is mostly wrong, the chain quickly flips—by step four, error dominates over correct.';\n      } else {\n        caption.textContent = 'High initial error means the chain is mostly wrong by the second step. Compounding makes recovery impossible downstream.';\n      }\n    }\n\n    slider.addEventListener('input', update);\n    update();\n  })();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  }
}
